,Not Recommended,272510,12129383,"Posted: 17 September, 2014",all,SirMadame,"DO NOT BUY.Worst purchase of the whole year. Judging from advertisements and trailers, this game could be considered scam.* NO Story mode besides 3 (VERY) short stories, which are done in under 1 hour.* VERY bad connection. The networking code of this game is horrible. Even if you have a perfect connection, depending on gamemode, you will share your connection speed with your opponent (meaning if he has lags, you have them too).This can result in battles being interrupted all 1-2 second by about 0,5 seconds with ""loading"" popups.Joining other people's lobbies will almost always result in a grave disadvantage for you due to noticable delays.*Only 4 gamemodes:1.) Online battles, which I described above.2.) World-Tournament mode, which actually is a mode in which you battle 4 times in each rank from D to S to be crowned best of the world. You can complete extremely short missions between the battles to either gain new comrades (must be done again for each character... ... ...) or to get some money (which is earned much much faster by simply bashing the A.I. in the VS mode over and over and over again) and items...By spending this money on any item on any shop you gain lottery tickets that are your main source for character customization items. It all comes down to a long grind that rewards you with a diminishing chance for new gear.3.) Free-for-All -> This is your Local VS Mode, either with friends or the A.I. (which is no match at all)4.) Ninja-""Escapades"" the sorry excuse for a story mode. Only 3 arcs of which one is just a cinematic with no content worthy to mention. All Episodes together have less than a dozen battles... I mean, c'mon.*The well anticipated character customization is broken down to choosing an outfit for your character (for example Naruto normal suit, non-combat clothes or samurai armor) and then sticking 3 items of your choice on them (you can choose upper left/right arm, face/masks and upper/lower torso on your back) - NO colour customization, NO renaming, NO haircuts.>>108 chars to choose from and they couldn't include a simple shinobi editor<<--> Huge disappointment.Oh well, you can choose from a wide variety of objects to use for your replacement jutsus (dodge mechanic in this game)... Doesn't matter that about 50% of those options is the normal one with a japanese Kanji-tag on them (SO mesmerizing...).[Kanji is one of the japanese ""alphabets""]*Each character has only 2 Jutsus: a normal one which knocks down your opponent (for example Rasengan for all Narutos) and an ultimate Nin-Jutsu which is a cinematic driven finishing move, which can be customized to include one of 4 short, voiced sentences accompanied by a static picture IF you finish your oppenent with it. (These 4 options must be unlocked via the lottery or gaining money)Depending on which outfit you choose for your character, these two jutsus differ (but only slightly most times, for example Naruto either uses his one clone Rasengan, Double-Rasengan in sage mode or his Rendan as pre-shippuden Naruto [Rendan is a humourus melee-combo utilizing his shadow clones])*On top of that are horrible, childish dialogues[---this game, even though you can toggle ""violence"" does have no blood whatsoever and all dialogues are cut down to ""are you happy?"" -no -> let's do something about it -> You DID something about it! -> you are my new BFF!---]*And ridiculously common loading screens, you will have to watch the loading icon after almost every action, this is NOT a joke, here is an example:[PLEASE BEAR IN MIND THIS WAS TESTED ON A TOP OF THE NODGE NEW COMPUTER; I EVEN MOUNTED A RAM DISK FOR JUST FOR THIS -> FASTEST POSSIBLE DISK ACCESS]::: You start the game, of course, it loads. 4 Logos (skippable), intro ""cinematic"" (skippable), loading screen, select game mode on main menu, loading screen, select action in submenu, loading screen (for this example I choose World Tournament mode), now you choose to either load your save or start a new game, LOADING SCREEN, skippable cinematic, skippable cinematic, loading screen, unnessecarily long dialogue with Shizune and Mabui at the beach. Now you can walk across the beach. From one end ot another it takes about 15 seconds run time... but still entering another areal of the tournament isle will start a LOADING sequence (at least this one is only about 1-2 seconds). Opening the menu has a severe delay of about 2-3 seconds, entering ANY subcthegory of this menu will show you a LOADING SCREEN. :::You get the idea?In addition to this, canceling out of most submenus will throw you back at the main menu for that game menu, even canceling out of a submenu will start a loading sequence...*And last but not least, several characters are severely imbalanced. Picking Deidara for example will yield you a win in about 80% of all fights by simply spamming your Kunai(ranged attack)-Action (Deidaras kunai special is a quickly spammable explosive-clay-bird barrage).*The only positive things about this game are1.) the massive roster of choosable shinobi (as said, 108), including all known kages, Madara, Obito (Tobi) and many child-versions of the Shippuden characters2.) the new network clone feature where you can customize up to 3 shinobi A.I. characters from which you can send out one at a time to gain levels and bring back items for you. The higher the level, the better the item.These clones are uploaded into a cloud and will appear randomly in games of other players (in world tournament mode these will stand around and wait for your challenge, in online mode, these will randomly appear after a fight and challenge you).Beating these clones will reward you that character, including their equipment. (Getting that badass greatsword to carry on my characters back from a random fight felt awesome... but that sword cannot be used, it is only decorational)I will say this as clear as I can: DO NOT BUYP.S.: If you only want to buy this for the playable characters, unlocking all of them only takes about one day of continously battling in any gamemode (If you win with S-Rank most of the time)."
