,Recommended,272510,12135055,"Posted: 17 September, 2014",all,Chaos1224,"To everyone who is complaining about the games lack of a story mode....THERE WAS NEVER ANY MENTION OF A STORY MODE EVER!!!! This game is a filler game, so that the developers would have more story to work with NS4. They did the exact same thing two years ago with Ninja storm generations. The only reason this game exists is so people will have something to hold them over until the next game comes out. So now that we got that out of the way, here is my review on the steam version of this game.Pros:-Improved combat systems. I play with gamepad so i cant really comment on how it is with M/K but the gamepad is smooth and plays great. They have changed things up a lot since NS3 so expect to be surprised when you start up a game. First and foremost there are 3 ways to play each character, Ultimate jutsu user, awakening user, and drive user (team battle only). Ultimate jutsu users can use their best attacks but wont be able to awaken, awaken users can awaken but cant use ultimate attacks, and drive users will rely heavily on their team mates and wont be able to awaken or use ultimate moves. The new system may seem weird to some people, i personally think its a good system. It mixes up the feel of the game and makes each battle a little different especially when playing online.-The tournament mode. Its great. I dont care what anyone says about it being awful, it really is the most unique thing the developers have done to this game that changes the gameplay so much that its actually worth replaying. The way the tournament is set up is, you have 4 teams. Each team has 3 members, and each has 1 person battle at a time. Each match will have 4 players fighting at once so it can get hectic. During these battles, there will be enviormental hazards and scenary that you can interact with to help hurt or help players win the battles. Outside of the battles, wondering the island holds different character events and different challenges to complete. On top of that, there is a story mode for the new mecha-naruto character. Its not that great of a story or that fun but it is there.-More characters-More stages-new music-can unlock characters outside of story mode buy earning money from battles. In case you hate the new tournament mode.-offers japanese voice options for characters and subtitle optionsCONS:-laggy. In combat there is no notice of lag at all, which is why i recommend this game. It is a fighting game afterall and thats where the core of the gameplay is. Outside however, the frames stutter pretty badly, characters will pop in and out even at close distances and it is especially distracting during the animated scenes where your better off skipping them.So thats it for my review. I really recommend that you get this game. If you are a fan of naruto and fighting games this is a must have.Edit: oh and if you are expereincing a slow down in the combat, turn off super sampaling. In fact, just leave it off. It doesnt add anything to the game and unless you have a powerful rig its just going to ruin your experience"
,Recommended,272510,12299006,"Posted: 30 September, 2014",all,NZ Denom,"I finally beat the game. The Escapades, Mecha-Naruto Story, The Tournament and the Ally Events. (But not all of the Challenges and Jobs, those are mindless Time-wasters.)Naruto Ultimate Ninja Storm Revolution was the most entertaining filler in my opinion. It made me laugh, cry (Literally..), and also made me.. very angry at times (that wore off after a while).The first thing i started with when i got this game was the ninja escapades. The anime scenes were quite entertaining, and felt like an actual episode of Naruto Shippudden. I like how they got rid of the quick time events for the cutscenes, i just wanted to sit back and relax after a fight i had won, I got that.. and more.The Akatsuki Origins were fun and easy to blast through, and it was fun to watch the cutscenes that played between each fight. The story of the Akatsuki origins in this game starts at the point where Deidara and the rest were just getting recruited and not before the Hanzo incident. Itachi and Kisame's joining wasn't included as well.The Itachi/Shisui Storyline was Incredibly entertaining to play through and watch, revealing facts and expanding on who Shisui was, and it includes some bonding between characters that.. I hate to say it, made me cry.. The good feels, ya know?After you finish the first two escapades, you are rewarded a short episode with team Minato, with Kushina.Now to the Mecha Naruto Story.. *sigh* Basically the type of story that was used in this has been dragged through countless arks and fillers.. Mecha naruto feels like an outsider, a freak and alone, and he feels just like Naruto did in the begining Bla Bla Bla. I'm not sorry for being harsh towards this story with Mecha Naruto, My feels were depleted after the legit Gaara story. It got less appealing to watch when it was recycled for Sora and Isaribi.Finally we get to the Tournament part. Basically, you mash buttons untill you win, in a 4 person arena where you collect orbs that Drop when you hit enemies and drop boxes.. Have fun repeating that untill you get that Ultimate Steam Achievements!!.. the game awards you small accesories that you can't equip unless you're playing as a character who's wearing their main costume.. Ultimate Customisation my a-.. sorry.While I enjoyed the Ninja Escapades A Lot, the rest was mildly entertaining at best.Because I played the Rise of a Ninja and The Broken Bond Games on the Xbox 360. I was not pleased with the free roam.. it was an annoyance, it was not fun, it was slow, it was lifeless, with the most boring side missions that included running from point A to B with fights thrown in.I'd give this game a 6/10. My scoring relies on the fun i had in the ninja escapades, the character roster, the lazy attempt at trying to appeal to the free roam thing they forgot that people wanted, and the Ultimate team moves that were thrown in for awesome fan service.My suggestion for the next game is to bring in some F@$%ing Voice acting!! This isn't a PS1/PSP game, Jeez. Pressing the prompt button to get the next speech bubble was Irritating, I was interested in what the characters had to say but in this case, the characters were hollow and without F@$%ING VOICE!!!!And please expand on the Free Roam (as in exploration and worthwhile bonuses, similar to UNS1 and The Xbox 360 Exclusives), you got the fighting mechanics down 100% and i am Greatful for that!! you can put some of your efforts elsewhere too now!!"
