76561198067638926,Not Recommended,272510,17555170,"Posted: 15 August, 2015",all,Sapherno11,"I can't recommend this game. For the 40 dollars I payed for it, it is NOT, worth it.Bascially, there are 4 highly...negative reasons why I really dislike the game, and two of them are actually gameplay mechanics that just ruined the game to the point I have uninstalled it, and will probably end up deleting it from my library and getting a refund.Point 1. Graphics. Honestly, while graphics are ""good"" Their almost exactly the same as the LAST game, there's no real increase here, and on top of that, almost all the characters look the same, and handle the same. This should be a Patch to the last game, not ""resold"" as a brand new game, because there's not a lot of new content here.Point 2. ""Custom"" character. Yes, you can customize your own character, just like Xenoverse!...wait, I have to use a regular Naruto Avatar, and I can't actually change anything, the only thing I can do is Add things? Sure, giving Naruto Shukaku's tail is funny, but for a ""character creator"" this was really half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥done, and more dissapointing then anything, plus the process of unlocking things FOR this creator is REALLY, really hard (as in you will pour HOURS, into trying to unlock a new tail, or hat, and even then, tis random chance if you get it, making it highly frustrating). At least Xenoverse gave you a set mission how to unlock something, here, you have to play a lottery, and HOPE you happen to get a usuable item out of it.Point 3. Storyline. The storyline while....interesting, was also Extremely short. It took perhaps 2-3 hours to complete at most. I was sorta hoping they'd have a good story, not something that I could clear in such a short amount of time.Point 4, and this is the point that just made me quit for good. World Tournement. (And ♥♥♥♥♥♥ AI programming). Honestly, this is just stupid, frustrating, irritating, and Extremely difficult. The tournement comes in different ""levels"" of difficulty. And you have to unlock characters by doing quests inside the ""tourny"". Overall, another irritating mechanic, but that's not what was upsetting. The tourney is basically 3 battles of 4 people going at it, so you create a team of 3 members, to duke out those 3 people with 4 other teams. That would be an interesting mechanic, except the Ai, especially at higher settings, WILL NOT TARGET ANYONE ELSE. That's right, it quickly stops being a free for all, and turns into a 1x3, ""AI attack player"" strategy. I got into the B rank of the Tourny, and won, before I finally said Screw this.Having 3 players constantly attack you is irritating, annoying, and makes the game Very hard to play. On top of that, because you actually have to UNLOCK characters by playing the game mode, you can't even use people you want IN battles. Personally I was looking forward to playing as Pain, but even after rank B, still don't have access to him.Overall, this was a highly frustrating experience, and not worth the 40 dollar pricetag I paid for it."
