,Recommended,272510,12433681,"Posted: 10 October, 2014",all,Who's that Pokémon?! - NaiOni,"While I generally recommend this game, I will ask you to take caution; this game does not run well on all PC's, and I am not talking about weaker machines. When I bought this game, I had the same problems I had with Ninja Storm 3 after I upgraded from my old Radeon HD 6950 1GB to a Radeon R9 290 4GB. From what I've gathered, these games do not run well on GPU's with a clockspeed that is too high, and will then run at a framerate as low as 20 FPS at worst. When in a fight, it will vary from 25-30 FPS. This not only means stuttering animation, but a lowered game speed as well, because the game speed is bound to the framerate, as is common practice in fighting games. I recommend this game to anyone with a slightly weaker system. If you DO have a stronger system, and decide to buy the game regardless, there are programs that can fix the problems. If you google ""ninja storm revolution framerate"" you'll find steam threads that can help you, although some of the instructions leave out some vital parts, so keep reading further in the threads."
