,Recommended,272510,18017921,"Posted: 13 September, 2015",all,Pyracious,"I like this a lot more than Ninja Storm 3 Full Burst. The Story doesn't feel like monotonous rehashed story elements from the manga, and much of the gameplay is in the tournament mode anyways which feels more like an pseudo-open-world environment. You can pretty much explore the tournament-mode map at your own leisure and help out other characters whom will then become available to support you in the battles ahead. You can also do some side missions for more money or explore the map and get items from things like floating balloons or stacks of mushrooms. Travel time is a bit tedious but there are NPCs to fast-travel between locations which helps alleviate it.There are tons of items to collect, both cosmetic and otherwise, and despite some cosmetic items being restricted on whom can wear them, it'd also be pretty silly having things like the Two-Tails Tail on Rock Lee or something so it's not like it doesn't make sense. There are also hundreds of items to customize your online profile that are super collectable.Albeit not a huge amount of new characters from the prior title, there are only so many characters that could be added from the series as after a point you're just creating movesets for characters that had a very small impact on the plotline and some others wouldn't make much sense as they've been dead for so long. Every character that someone would really want to play that I can forsee is included that were known at release. And some that people might want as characters are indirectly available as transformations (the tailed beasts).The gameplay itself is pretty cool too. The tournament-mode capture the most orbs style allows you to give it your all and it's not over until the timer ends, In the multi-round tournaments, you can also come back from a huge loss in the prior round just by playing better on your current round character, which is nice. This is quite unlike prior 4-man gamemodes where if you ran out of health you're out, which is no fun at all. It does reward ranged large-aoe attacks more, but a small price to pay for a more varied and less punishing gamemode. In the case that you want more normal matches where you remove your foes health to win, most of the game outside of the tournaments is like that.The only aspects I'd like more is some other ways to unlock characters than simply stockpiling money, and maybe different outfits for some characters that otherwise have none. A more clear difficulty for each recruitment mission before starting it would also be helpful so you know what to expect to an extent and can prepare accordingly, as some of them can be pretty challenging for a new player.I'd give the game an 9/10 overall. The issues I have with it are trivial and it fulfills my expectations of an anime-based fighting game in almost every way."
