,Recommended,272510,12382586,"Posted: 5 October, 2014",all,KageYuuki,"I should probably preface this with the fact that this is the first Naruto fighting game I've bought since Clash of Ninja 2 for the Gamecube. I can safely say these games have certainly come a long way since then.Story:The game has its own story that it follows; think filler episodes in the anime. There are two story modes in the game: the Ninja World Tournament's mecha Naruto, and the stories in Ninja Escapades. The cut scenes in Escapes were done in the same style as the show and sheds some light on a few areas not covered in the show or manga. I did find it to be a little too short, only taking a couple hours to get through. Though in the game's defense, there isn't much more new canon left that it could have followed and what there is will likely be for a later game.Sound:Being able to pick between English and Japanese versions for the voiceovers is a great option to have. Everyone has their own preference between the two version of the show. However, the music is probably the area I found myself being the most disappointed in. The soundtrack doesn't offer much in terms of variety; I was often just listening to the same few tracks over and over again. After a few hours of gameplay, I ended up just muting it and playing my own music.Gameplay:What do you think of when you hear Ninja World Tournament? Chances are the last thing that comes to mind will trying to be the one with the most orbs collected when the time runs out. While the four person, free-for-all style battles that take place in this mode can be difficult, I felt they were wasted being only used for nabbing orbs. The combo system is another area that felt lacking. To pull off combos in the game you use the b button and, depending on the combo, tilt the control stick up or down once.Overall, I still found this a fun fighting game with a huge cast of characters to choose from. The different modes found under Free Battle help to add some variety and would certainly be fun to play against friends in. While the music certainly is disappointing, I wouldn't say it ruined the game. I recommend this if you're looking for a fan of Naruto and looking for a good way to kill some time."
