,Not Recommended,272510,14738518,"Posted: 4 March, 2015",all,Octanic,"The game itself has a good part and a bad one.Good parts:- You can play with almost every character on the shippuden series (even the dead ones)- you can perform new jutsus when you select an specific group of characters (ex: when you choose the 3 Sannin, you can use a very nice ultimate jutsu)- there are new stuff you can watch to understand even more the Naruto universe- you can collect stuff so you have more things to do- you can have a network clone and show everyone how good you can build a character using the items and combinations- if you're tired from the story mode, you can freely battle with any character you want (as long as you play the game, you unlock more characters for free play)- there are jobs and you must battle everyone to get characters to help you on battles- the controls are easy to learn, and you can perform nice combos without having to smash every button on your controller/keyboard, which happens with a lot of games of this genre.- it has exclusive new jutsus, like Minato's Flying Raijin: Jiku Shippu Senko Rennodan ZeroshikiBad:- lacks performance during online battles (it is horrible, I mean, how can they manage to make it so stiff to play? I am a very addicted player, and I can have a good control of the battle. But when I tried the online mode, I got my butt kicked, because it was so sluggish that I could not perform a basic combo!)- the orb system is boring and broken. You start playing, it's kinda ok. But when you get to rank S, it is REAL boring to play, because there are no new challenges, and the NPC enemy gang up on you, and all you get to do is to dodge all your way hoping who is attacking you get trapped or step on the traps you lay down.- It is not a real story mode with last boss. Mecha naruto story has it, but anyway, you gotta play the boring orb battles first- the characters characteristics does not match what you have on naruto universe.- if you did not see the entire series, you will have a lot of spoilers. It is not really a bad one to consider, but you will be very disappointed when you begin to know something you are not supposed to.- the drive and awakening battle type feels weaker than the ultimate combo one. I don't know if it is a personal issue, but ultimate jutsu battle type is much more easier to fight than the other types.My final words: If you have played Naruto Ninja Storm 3 Full Burst, you will find out this one is REALLY BORING! Ok, we have new jutsus, a great improvement on avoidability mechanics (RT does the strafing), but no. I thought this was a good game until I played his antecessor full burst. And it made me very upset."
