,Recommended,272510,20793874,"Posted: 27 January, 2016",all,2dumb2die,"i have to say, i enjoy all the naruto storm games i've played and each installment i'd say is better than the last. they put in new charcters so there is that to look forward to as well as new arenas and new things you can make your own character wear so you can be even more unique from otehr people.the game runs super well, and the fights are both fast and fun, and it's a blast to play through. this game, unlike NUNS 3, doesn't really have a story mode, but none of the others before it really copied over the same story repeatedly. you could insert a dragonball Z story from every game that's ever come out. this one does however have a few little side stories such as a new charcter to the universe based around the main mode of the game as well as a few clips followed by fights that give back story to how things came to be.the main mode of this game is a tournament based story.... 'story' ther isn't really much to it other than ""go into a rank of an arena and fight a few fights against 3 other opponents."" it's really more of you fighting 2 computers that are in a battle royal where you try to get teh most orbs, basically your score for endgame, and the one with the most wins. when you finish a rank you can continue the.... 'story' and get to unlock the next rank to fight in. this includes new traps or obsticales to make fighting the computers harder.ther are other modes such as tournaments, leagues, as well as sruvival where you last as long as you can against waves of enemies or until you get beat out in an endless fight. there is also online where you can obviously fight other players and a place to customize your charcters, and each version/costume/whatever can have their own 3 differnt custom looks with items they wear, things they substitue with, or even finishing scenes when you get and ultimate finsh.i can say for certain, after going for every achievement that the tournament stuff, the 'story' mode really isn't that hard. the higher the difficulty the more hazards you need to watch out for, but the more stuff the ai can get tripped up on and lose their orbs for you to just swoop in and steal free points. several times, eve on the challenges i never needed to do more than doge and dash for a whole round since it was easier to let them beat the snot out of one another or just get blasted by traps.that does bring me to what i would say is the last thing i can think of to talk aobut here and that is the ai.when they are on low difficulty, they aren't too resistant or aggressive, but oin higher difficulties they can basically cheat to fight. i want to call it true artificial difficulty because the only reason i seem to have trouble with fighting computer opponents and the like in survivalk where you need to win and beat all oponenets to win is because they can do things in split seconds that take you longer to do. some of the problems being, instant chakra dashes, so they can cancel your dash without you having seen them load chakra or things like, when you subtstitute and get behind them they can instantaniously dash into you and continue their combo. they can literally do this and sub from your attacks and still be at an advantage because they can do things that aren't physically possible.really, it's an amazingly fun game, and even better with friends, and it's awesome to see what you can do to make more unique combos using dashes, cancels, justsu and the like. and even though it's fun even fighting ai, they can be really cheap and unfair only because it makes it harder for you to win. but it's not really a fair and realistic chalenge where you feel great having won because you can't really get an opening out of them.last thing too, forgot to say so. if you are trying to grind out the achievements liek i did, i will say taht it is TEDIOUS! i swear most of the time i took longer to go from fight to fight than it did for me to actually beat it and go on to the next one. just be warned, if you have any desire to power through and get things in this game, you'll most likely spend more of your time sighing because you just want to be done with somethign that takes 3 times as long as it should to complete."
