,Recommended,272510,17582477,"Posted: 17 August, 2015",all,Jardon,"First off this game is nothing short of beautiful.  The graphics are incredible and the menus are genius.  This was something that was true of ultimate ninja storm 3 and it seems that  its strengths have been brought to this game which makes me beyond happy.  As for the gameplay, improvements have been made such as combat types and customization.The story however is nearly a joke.  This is the reason I did not buy it at release.  The price tag was too high for what I believed I was getting and I was right.  Dont get me wrong, the developers deserve to get paid for what they made.  This game has some great strengths, but happens to fall short in a few places.  It felt much like I was getting just the combat that was in ultimate ninja storm 3 but with a few weeks worth of work making it look like a new game.   it is way too much reliant on the combat for sustenance.  Anything outside of combat is just a bare, shallow way to get you to the next fight.Also combat poses no real challenge is 99% of the battles.  Either the ai blows or the user is too strong.  I think its a little bit of both.  The only enemies that could be difficult are those who are range heavy.  Also awakening for some characters is op which i think is why the drive mode was added.  Drive mode however is still not enough with the ai behind it.My favorite Naruto game is by far Rise of a Ninja.  In that game combat was fun and outside of combat actually felt like it had a point to it.  There were fun missions (unlike the side missions in revolution), hidden items, and a cast of characters that were a joy to interact with.  I know that this is shippudden and things are much more serious than in rise of a ninja, but at the same time it lacks the fun, adventurous feel that made the game a joy to play.I would recommend this game if not only to support the presence of naruto games on steam.  The game is far from perfect, but still offers a enjoyable experience with a lower price tag."
,Recommended,272510,17755647,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,Super Shark Face,"I'm a fan of the show, so I bought this game.  If you're a fan, you'll probably like it.  There are so many characters in this game, and it's really fun to run around as your favorite characters, fight as them with their special techniques and ""decorate"" them with accessories that are references to stuff in the show.  There are also parts of the game that have cool storylines (there are small tidbits in the Tournament, as well as longer ones in the Scenarios mode).Even if you're not a fan of the show, the gameplay is really great.  I haven't played many other fighting games so I can't compare it to anything, but there are so many different mechanics and it doesn't feel like you're just button-mashing to win.  I really like the one-on-one battles the best, but the four player battles are similar to coin mode in smash bros and are also pretty fun.One thing that I thought the game could've done better is the tutorial.  I basically learned how to do everything from reading the tips during the loading screens.  There were so many huge things I missed because they were glossed over: chakra dash (Y+A), the substitution jutsu (RB), even that you can recharge your chakra (hold down Y).  Also, if you pick a ranged character, make sure you hit X as your primary button or you'll be wondering why your ranged character has no ranged moves.  I didn't figure out any of these things until the B-rank of the tournament... yeah....Once you figure out all of the controls and possible moves though, this game is great fun even in offline.  I haven't played online yet but I'm planning to try it (and probably get destroyed)."
