,Recommended,272510,30179159,Posted: 25 February,all,spiralstorm97248,"** ATTENTION ALL NARUTO FANS AND PLAYERS ALIKE **This review may contain spoilers and comparison information regarding other similar games to this one. Read at your own discretion...Now, under normal circumstances, I don't review single-player games unless...1: They are absolutely awesome or terrible (Glitches notwithstanding) or...2: I can compare them to an identical or similar multiplayer game I have played or also actively play. This being said, NARUTO SHIPPUDEN: Ultimate Ninja STORM Revolution will be compared and contrasted from/to...1: NARUTO Online. 2: NARUTO Saga/NARUTO Spirit. So here goes...NARUTO SHIPPUDEN: Ultimate Ninja STORM Revolution quite possibly has the best graphics and most playable characters out of any NARUTO game I've ever played. It is also VERY IMPORTANT for one to remember this is a FIGHTING GAME, so exploration of many areas is going to be quite limited, unlike in the game NARUTO Online, where there are several notable areas of the shinobi world one can freely explore in spite of the simpler (But well-done) graphics. Nevertheless, you are able to run around and even jump up to/down from higher or lower places at your leisure. The fighting here is also going to be fast-paced; be aware of this and be prepared to change your battle tactics (And perhaps your control configurations) in order to suit your foes' weaknesses. Unlockable characters include...1: At least a few of the Kage. 2: Several variations of Naruto and other notable ninja, including most members of the Akatsuki, and even Madara Uchiha! There are also a few different modes, including the notable Ninja Escapades, which play out much like a typical NARUTO Arc. The downside of this (And every game has a downside) is the inability to explore different areas during the Escapades. In fact, the last Escapade is only a cut-scene with no player interaction whatsoever. The mode which actually DOES allow for some exploration is the Mecha-Naruto Story, which isn't as fun, because of the inability to select your characters as you see fit. And speaking of which...You cannot create your own characters either; you have to make use of the ones provided and unlock additional characters as you progress through the game. Kind of disappointing, but again, similar to NARUTO Online. On there, you CAN sort-of create your own character and shape him or her pretty-much to your liking. One can do the same with NARUTO Saga/NARUTO Spirit, however, I would NOT recommend playing NARUTO Saga/NARUTO Spirit AT ALL!! The story and graphics on there are VERY POORLY DONE; you have to shell out real money to gain access to Naruto himself; the Hidden Leaf Village looks NOTHING like it should; and, to top it all off, the Ninja you DO gain access to are nothing but enemies to Team 7!! Why would anyone want Mizuki on their team!? Come on!! Anyway, I would recommend NARUTO SHIPPUDEN: Ultimate Ninja STORM Revolution for the Ninja Escapades, if nothing else. Otherwise, good luck unlocking all those talented ninja. You'll need it! ;-)"
