76561198074931496,Recommended,272510,35013988,Posted: 16 September,all,X'Vazr,"I'm not sure I'd want to pay full price, but I got this on sale, and I'm really enjoying it. I got it more because I liked Naruto than because I particularly love fighting games, but I find the game mechanics engaging and fun. It seems to me that, with the recharge mechanics for various actions, combat has a light tactical feel. For me, this is a plus; I don't especially enjoy games that value twitch reflexes over all else. (...My favorite games ever were Medieval Totar War and Heroes 3).I find the game very nice looking, the colors and designs more vibrant and interesting than in the anime itself. In ~13 hours I've had two crashes, both in a row, and no other stability problems. In a few cut scenes I've noticed visual stutters, but that's about it for technical complaints.I do have two larger gripes:(1) The variety of characters is undercut by the fact that some of them are very similar. E.g. There are at least four different narutos -- not Naruto costumes, but Naruto characters, and I think a comparable number of Gaaras. It's really not that I find the variety of characters bad, just that the claim to 100 playable characters doesn't mean as much as it might seem. That said, I do enjoy that it's not super complicated unlocking new characters; you can get most by playing any mode.(2) I wish there were a tutorial and/or a more detailed game manual. There are some modes/mechanics that I still haven't managed to figure out by playing, and I wish there were a text searchable pdf where I could read about them."
